        "segment": "The MSL tool supported automated execution by simulating process scenarios and enforcing rules to ensure process integrity.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "By changing the rules and executing a scenario repeatedly, the timings were compared and contrasted, leading to significant process improvement without major investment in resources.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Prescriptive process models are prescriptions for the way software development should progress, outlining how the process ought to be conducted.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Some are prescriptions for the way software development should progress",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Descriptive process models are descriptions of the way software development is actually done in practice.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "others are descriptions of the way software development is done in actuality",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The purpose of building a process model is to help the team understand the gap between what should be (prescriptive) and what is (descriptive).",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Building a process model and discussing its subprocesses help the team understand the gap between what should be and what is.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "bullet_intro",
        "segment": "The purposes of modeling a process include",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "There are several other reasons for modeling a process:",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "bullet",
        "segment": "Forming a common understanding of the activities, resources, and constraints involved in software development.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "When a group writes down a description of its development process, it forms a common understanding of the activities, resources, and constraints involved in software development.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "bullet",
        "segment": "Finding inconsistencies, redundancies, and omissions in the process and its parts to make the process more effective and focused.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Creating a process model helps the development team find inconsistencies, redundancies, and omissions in the process and in its constituent parts. As these problems are noted and corrected, the process becomes more effective and focused on building the final product.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "bullet",
        "segment": "Reflecting the goals of development, such as building high-quality software, finding faults early, and meeting budget and schedule constraints.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The model should reflect the goals of development, such as building high-quality software, finding faults early in development, and meeting required budget and schedule constraints.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "bullet",
        "segment": "Tailoring the process for the special situation in which it will be used.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Every process should be tailored for the special situation in which it will be used. Building a process model helps the development team understand where that tailoring is to occur.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "It is appropriate to use prescriptive models when defining how the software development process should be conducted to meet goals and standards.",
        "citations": []
    },
