[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The Loan Arranger system involves a central repository of loan information that is updated regularly with reports from lenders and accessed by multiple loan analysts simultaneously.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The Loan Arranger system contains a repository of information about loans from a variety of lenders.This repository may be empty.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The Loan Arranger system may be used by up to four loan analysts simultaneously.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Therefore, the Repository architectural style is a valid choice because it views the system as a central data store (the portfolio of loans) with mechanisms for storing, retrieving, and updating the data.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Repository, since it will be convenient to view the system as a central data store (the portfolio of loans) with mechanisms for storing, retrieving, and updating the data.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The system must allow multiple loan analysts to view and manipulate the same data concurrently, which aligns well with the Client-Server architectural style that supports multiple clients accessing shared data.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The Loan Arranger system may be used by up to four loan analysts simultaneously.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Client-Server, since this design style would be a convenient way to allow many different loan analysts to view the same data in different ways.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The Object-Oriented architectural style is also valid because it allows certain features, such as data structures holding bank information, to be updated independently without affecting other components.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Object-Oriented, since this design style would allow certain features to be updated (for example, the data structures holding the bank information) while requiring no changes to other components in the system.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Hence, all three architectural styles—Object-Oriented, Client-Server, and Repository—are valid choices for the Loan Arranger system.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "a, b, and c",
